java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>, java.util.RandomAccess
public class SortedList<T>
extends java.util.ArrayList<T>

An implementation of a Sorted List, which extends ArrayList. It is constructed using a Comparator object that can compare two objects together, thus allowing the SortedList to order its elements into ascending or descending order. We can also create a SortedList without a Comparator object, if and only if the objects to be used implement the Comparable interface.

Author:
Matthew Kelly (Badgerati).
